title: Frieze, 1905–15
inscribed: Printed in selvedge: "S.A. Maxwell & Co. New York & Chicago." "Exclusive Design No-.3510 S"
description: Alternating large and small yellow rose bouquets surrounded by green foliate scrolls and floral swags. Background of solid dark red stripes that gradually transform to dots and terminate at top bands of scallops and scrolls. The top has stripes and floral swags. Ground shades from dark pink to cream (bottom to top).

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper.. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-510.
